pageexchange-logdesc: This is the log of actions related to the Page Exchange extension.
pageexchange-installed: A section header for packages that have been installed on the wiki
pageexchange-available:
A section header for packages that are available to be installed on the wiki
{{identical|Available}}
pageexchange-nonmatching: A section header for packages that can be installed on the wiki, but which require MediaWiki extensions that this wiki does not have
pageexchange-unusable: A section header for packages that cannot be installed on the wiki, for technical reasons
pageexchange-alreadyexist: A note placed above a list of external wiki pages that could be imported to this wiki
pageexchange-installpackage:
An edit summary. Parameters:
* $1 - the name of a "package" of wiki pages
pageexchange-updatepackage:
An edit summary. Parameters:
* $1 - the name of a "package" of wiki pages
pageexchange-uninstallpackage:
An edit summary. Parameters:
* $1 - the name of a "package" of wiki pages
pageexchange-installpackagelog:
A log action description. The first parameter is ignored. Parameters:
* $2 - the name of a "package" of wiki pages
* $3 - the name of the creator of this package
pageexchange-updatepackagelog:
A log action description. The first parameter is ignored. Parameters:
* $2 - the name of a "package" of wiki pages
* $3 - the name of the creator of this package
pageexchange-uninstallpackagelog:
A log action description. The first parameter is ignored. Parameters:
* $2 - the name of a "package" of wiki pages
* $3 - the name of the creator of this package
pageexchange-jsonfileerror:
An error message. Parameters:
* $1 - the URL of a JSON file
* $2 - the error that occurred when attempting to read the file
pageexchange-package-additionalslots: A label in a display; "slots" refers to MediaWiki's [https://www.mediawiki.org/wiki/Manual:Slot multi-content revisions slots]
pageexchange-package-requiredextensions: A label for the list of MediaWiki extensions required for this package to work
pageexchange-package-requiredpackages: A label for the list of wiki page "packages" that must be installed for the current package to work
pageexchange-package-externaltext: A link to text that could be imported to a local wiki page
pageexchange-package-externalfile: A link to an outside file that could be uploaded to this wiki
pageexchange-package-morerecent: An info message about a "package" of wiki pages that has been installed on this wiki
pageexchange-pagehaschanged: An info message, displayed right after the name of the page
pageexchange-textcontents: A link to the text of a page in the File: namespace (rather than to the file itself)
pageexchange-localcopymatches: An info message, displayed after the name of a page
pageexchange-localcopydiffers: An info message, displayed after the name of a page
pageexchange-localfileunknown: An info message, needed because this code cannot compare two different files to see if they are the same
pageexchange-latestvalue:
A message that says what the most recent value is for an attribute whose value can change at any time. Parameters:
* $1 - the most recent value
pageexchange-uninstallablepackage: The header of a warning message
pageexchange-packageidnull: An error message when URL misses a necessary parameter
pageexchange-packagenotexists: An error message when no package exists
pageexchange-packagealreadyinstalled: An info message that package is already installed
